rs\";i:5;s:13:\"custom-header\";i:6;s:11:\"custom-menu\";i:7;s:12:\"editor-style\";i:8;s:21:\"featured-image-header\";i:9;s:15:\"featured-images\";i:10;s:15:\"flexible-header\";i:11;s:20:\"front-page-post-form\";i:12;s:19:\"full-width-template\";i:13;s:12:\"microformats\";i:14;s:12:\"post-formats\";i:15;s:20:\"rtl-language-support\";i:16;s:11:\"sticky-post\";i:17;s:13:\"theme-options\";i:18;s:17:\"threaded-comments\";i:19;s:17:\"translation-ready\";}s:7:\"Subject\";a:3:{i:0;s:7:\"holiday\";i:1;s:13:\"photoblogging\";i:2;s:8:\"seasonal\";}}','yes'),(161,'theme_mods_zerif-lite','a:49:{i:0;b:0;s:18:\"nav_menu_locations\";a:1:{s:7:\"primary\";i:2;}s:10:\"zerif_logo\";s:87:\"http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/logo_01-pb.jpg\";s:13:\"zerif_address\";s:138:\"<a href=\"http://www.westsideireland.com\" target=\"_blank\">Unit 6, Monksland Business Centre, Monksland, Athlone, Co. Roscommon, Ireland</a>\";s:11:\"zerif_email\";s:70:\"<a href=\"mailto:contact@andreramosbjj.ie\">contact@andreramosbjj.ie</a>\";s:11:\"zerif_phone\";s:48:\"<a href=\"tel:+353894932520\">+353 89 493 2520</a>\";s:19:\"zerif_accessibility\";s:1:\"1\";s:15:\"zerif_copyright\";s:31:\"Andre Ramos BJJ (andreramos.ie)\";s:19:\"zerif_bigtitle_show\";s:0:\"\";s:19:\"zerif_parallax_show\";s:0:\"\";s:20:\"zerif_bigtitle_title\";s:42:\"Welcome to andre ramos brazilian jiu jitsu\";s:30:\"zerif_bigtitle_redbutton_label\";s:8:\"programs\";s:32:\"zerif_bigtitle_greenbutton_label\";s:12:\"get in touch\";s:16:\"background_image\";s:99:\"http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/horizontal-thin-normal.png\";s:17:\"background_repeat\";s:8:\"repeat-y\";s:21:\"background_position_x\";s:4:\"left\";s:21:\"background_attachment\";s:6:\"scroll\";s:20:\"zerif_ourfocus_title\";s:8:\"Programs\";s:23:\"zerif_ourfocus_subtitle\";s:305:\"Training in an unorganized environment can be extremely frustrating and overwhelming. At the Andre Ramos BJJ team we don\'t just teach people how to fight, we give people the necessary guidance and class structure for the  student to enjoy maximum benefit and, of course, have fun with Brazilian Jiu Jitsu.\";s:18:\"zerif_aboutus_show\";s:0:\"\";s:19:\"zerif_aboutus_title\";s:9:\"About BJJ\";s:22:\"zerif_aboutus_subtitle\";s:126:\"\"The Jiu Jitsu I created was designed to give the weak ones a chance to face the heavy and strong.\" (Gran Master Helio Gracie)\";s:26:\"zerif_aboutus_biglefttitle\";s:81:\"You should never have a power, in any area, with the purpose of harming someone. \";s:18:\"zerif_aboutus_text\";s:1405:\"Helio Gracie, the youngest son of Gastão and Cesalina Gracie\'s eight children (three were girls), was always a very physically frail child. He would run up a flight of stairs and have fainting spells, and no one could figure out why.  At age fourteen, he moved in with his older brothers who lived and taught Jiu-Jitsu in a house in Botafogo, a borough of Rio de Janeiro. Following doctor’s recommendations, Helio would spend the next few years limited to only watching his brothers teach.         One day, when Helio was 16 years old, a student showed up for class when Carlos was not around. Helio, who had memorized all the techniques from watching his brothers teach, offered to start the class. When the class was over, Carlos showed up and apologized for his delay. The student answered, \"No problem. I enjoyed the class with Helio very much and, if you don\'t mind, I\'d like to continue learning from him.\" Carlos agreed, and Helio became an instructor. Helio soon realized that due to his frail physique, most of the techniques he had learned from watching Carlos teach were particularly difficult for him to execute. Eager to make the techniques work for him, he began modifying them to accommodate his weak body. Emphasizing the use of leverage and timing over strength and speed, Helio modified virtually all of the techniques and, through trial and error, created Gracie/Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu.\";s:27:\"zerif_aboutus_feature1_text\";s:0:\"\";s:25:\"zerif_aboutus_feature1_nr\";s:0:\"\";s:25:\"zerif_aboutus_feature2_nr\";s:3:\"100\";s:25:\"zerif_aboutus_feature3_nr\";s:3:\"100\";s:25:\"zerif_aboutus_feature4_nr\";s:3:\"100\";s:28:\"zerif_aboutus_feature1_title\";s:0:\"\";s:28:\"zerif_aboutus_feature2_title\";s:0:\"\";s:28:\"zerif_aboutus_feature3_title\";s:0:\"\";s:28:\"zerif_aboutus_feature4_title\";s:0:\"\";s:19:\"zerif_ourteam_title\";s:11:\"Instructors\";s:22:\"zerif_ourteam_subtitle\";s:0:\"\";s:20:\"zerif_contactus_show\";s:0:\"\";s:24:\"zerif_contactus_subtitle\";s:90:\"Interested? Send us an email with all your doubts. It will be a pleasure to help you out! \";s:21:\"zerif_contactus_email\";s:18:\"vgabdala@gmail.com\";s:28:\"zerif_contactus_button_label\";s:4:\"Send\";s:30:\"zerif_contactus_recaptcha_show\";i:1;s:23:\"zerif_contactus_sitekey\";s:0:\"\";s:25:\"zerif_contactus_secretkey\";s:0:\"\";s:30:\"zerif_bigtitle_greenbutton_url\";s:54:\"http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/#contact\";s:18:\"zerif_address_icon\";s:90:\"http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/westside-logo.png\";s:23:\"zerif_testimonials_show\";s:1:\"1\";s:21:\"zerif_socials_twitter\";s:0:\"\";s:22:\"zerif_socials_linkedin\";s:0:\"\";s:21:\"zerif_socials_behance\";s:0:\"\";s:22:\"zerif_socials_dribbble\";s:0:\"\";}','yes'),(162,'widget_ctup-ads-widget','a:5:{i:1;a:4:{s:5:\"title\";s:11:\"BJJ Classes\";s:4:\"text\";s:271:\"BJJ promotes the concept that a smaller, weaker person can successfully defend against a bigger, stronger assailant by using proper technique, leverage, and most notably, taking the fight to the ground, and then applying joint-locks and chokeholds to defeat the opponent.\";s:4:\"link\";s:1:\"#\";s:9:\"image_uri\";s:100:\"http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/BJJ-Icon-e1455395165789.jpg\";}i:2;a:4:{s:5:\"title\";s:10:\"BJJ 4 Kids\";s:4:\"text\";s:159:\"For children between the ages of 5 and 13, BJJ 4 Kids emphasizes discipline, responsibility, and respect. And, the most important, they will MOVE and have FUN!\";s:4:\"link\";s:1:\"#\";s:9:\"image_uri\";s:105:\"http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/bjj4kids_icon-e1455395002692.png\";}i:3;a:4:{s:5:\"title\";s:4:\"BJJ \";s:4:\"text\";s:164:\"Showcase your team, products, clients, about info, testimonials, latest posts from the blog, contact form, additional calls to action. Everything translation ready.\";s:4:\"link\";s:1:\"#\";s:9:\"image_uri\";s:96:\"http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosmidwest.ie/wp-content/themes/zerif-lite/images/ccc.png\";}i:4;a:4:{s:5:\"title\";s:11:\"MMA Classes\";s:4:\"text\";s:212:\"BJJ can be used for grappling tournaments (gi and no-gi) and mixed martial arts (MMA) competition or self-defense. Learn MMA techniques with an experienced Andre Ramos BJJ coach and MMA fighter Claiton Rodrigues.\";s:4:\"link\";s:1:\"#\";s:9:\"image_uri\";s:100:\"http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/mma_icon-e1455394753351.png\";}s:12:\"_multiwidget\";i:1;}','yes'),(163,'widget_zerif_testim-widget','a:4:{i:1;a:5:{s:5:\"title\";s:9:\"Teste 123\";s:4:\"text\";s:242:\"Cum sociis natoque penatibus et magnis dis parturient montes, nascetur ridiculus mus. Curabitur nec sem vel sapien venenatis mattis non vitae augue. Nullam congue commodo lorem vitae facilisis. Suspendisse malesuada id turpis interdum dictum.\";s:9:\"image_uri\";s:98:\"http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/wp-content/themes/zerif-lite/images/testimonial1.jpg\";s:7:\"details\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"Linda Guthrie\";s:4:\"text\";s:242:\"Cum sociis natoque penatibus et magnis dis parturient montes, nascetur ridiculus mus. Curabitur nec sem vel sapien venenatis mattis non vitae augue. Nullam congue commodo lorem vitae facilisis. Suspendisse malesuada id turpis interdum dictum.\";s:9:\"image_uri\";s:98:\"http://loca