INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1,1,'2016-02-07 23:28:14','2016-02-07 23:28:14','<img src=\"http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/brazil-flag-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"brazil-flag\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-106\" />\r\n\r\nWe have launched our newest website. We hope to keep it up to date as much as possible! \r\nPlease come over for a visit, first training day is free! \r\n\r\nTeam Andre Ramos midwest.','Welcome!','','publish','closed','closed','','welcome','','','2016-08-17 16:22:14','2016-08-17 15:22:14','',0,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?p=1',0,'post','',0),(2,1,'2016-02-07 23:28:14','2016-02-07 23:28:14','This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosmidwest.ie/wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!','Sample Page','','publish','closed','open','','sample-page','','','2016-02-07 23:28:14','2016-02-07 23:28:14','',0,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(4,1,'2016-02-07 23:30:15','2016-02-07 23:30:15','','logo_01','','inherit','open','closed','','logo_01','','','2016-02-07 23:30:38','2016-02-07 23:30:38','',0,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/logo_01.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(5,1,'2016-02-07 23:46:11','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2016-02-07 23:46:11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?p=5',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(6,1,'2016-02-07 23:46:11','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2016-02-07 23:46:11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?p=6',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(7,1,'2016-02-07 23:47:08','2016-02-07 23:47:08','//TODO','Brazilian Jiu Jitsu','','publish','closed','closed','','brazilian-jiu-jitsu','','','2016-02-07 23:47:08','2016-02-07 23:47:08','',0,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?page_id=7',0,'page','',0),(8,1,'2016-02-07 23:47:08','2016-02-07 23:47:08','//TODO','Brazilian Jiu Jitsu','','inherit','closed','closed','','7-revision-v1','','','2016-02-07 23:47:08','2016-02-07 23:47:08','',7,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/2016/02/07/7-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(9,1,'2016-02-07 23:47:33','2016-02-07 23:47:33','//TODO','BJJ 4 Kids','','publish','closed','closed','','bjj-4-kids','','','2016-02-07 23:47:33','2016-02-07 23:47:33','',0,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?page_id=9',0,'page','',0),(10,1,'2016-02-07 23:47:33','2016-02-07 23:47:33','//TODO','BJJ 4 Kids','','inherit','closed','closed','','9-revision-v1','','','2016-02-07 23:47:33','2016-02-07 23:47:33','',9,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/2016/02/07/9-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(11,1,'2016-02-07 23:48:00','2016-02-07 23:48:00','//TODO','Our Instructors','','publish','closed','closed','','our-instructors','','','2016-02-07 23:48:00','2016-02-07 23:48:00','',0,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?page_id=11',0,'page','',0),(12,1,'2016-02-07 23:48:00','2016-02-07 23:48:00','//TODO','Our Instructors','','inherit','closed','closed','','11-revision-v1','','','2016-02-07 23:48:00','2016-02-07 23:48:00','',11,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/2016/02/07/11-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(13,1,'2016-02-07 23:48:27','2016-02-07 23:48:27','<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?page_id=25\">White Belts</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?page_id=27\">Blue Belts</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?page_id=29\">Purple Belts</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?page_id=31\">Brown Belts</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?page_id=33\">Black Belts</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n','Meet the Team','','publish','closed','closed','','meet-the-team','','','2016-08-17 16:36:05','2016-08-17 15:36:05','',0,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?page_id=13',0,'page','',0),(14,1,'2016-02-07 23:48:27','2016-02-07 23:48:27','//TODO','Meet the Team','','inherit','closed','closed','','13-revision-v1','','','2016-02-07 23:48:27','2016-02-07 23:48:27','',13,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/2016/02/07/13-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(19,1,'2016-02-07 23:49:50','2016-02-07 23:49:50','Mixed martial arts (MMA) is a full-contact combat sport that allows both striking and grappling, both standing and on the ground, using techniques from other combat sports and martial arts. \r\n\r\nOriginally promoted as a competition to find the most effective martial arts for real unarmed combat, competitors from different fighting styles were pitted against one another in contests with relatively few rules. \r\n\r\nLater, individual fighters employed multiple martial arts into their style. MMA promoters were pressured to adopt additional rules to increase competitors\' safety, to comply with sport regulations and to broaden mainstream acceptance of the sport.\r\n\r\nFollowing these changes, the sport has seen increased popularity with a pay-per-view business that rivals boxing and professional wrestling.','Mixed Martial Arts','','publish','closed','closed','','competition-training','','','2016-08-17 15:41:13','2016-08-17 14:41:13','',0,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?page_id=19',0,'page','',0),(20,1,'2016-02-07 23:49:50','2016-02-07 23:49:50','//TODO','Competition Training','','inherit','closed','closed','','19-revision-v1','','','2016-02-07 23:49:50','2016-02-07 23:49:50','',19,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/2016/02/07/19-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(21,1,'2016-02-07 23:50:16','2016-02-07 23:50:16','<strong>Overview</strong>\r\n\r\nBrazilian Jiu Jitsu promotes the concept that a smaller, weaker person can successfully defend against a bigger, stronger assailant by using leverage and proper technique.\r\n\r\nMany students first learn about jiu jitsu through the great popularity of mixed martial arts (MMA) competition, where Brazilian Jiu Jitsu technique is very prominent. Indeed, the beginnings of the contemporary MMA competition were largely tied up with proving the combat-efficiency of Brazilian Jiu Jitsu. \r\n\r\nThe practice of Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu as a sport, however, is strongly separated from MMA. Daily classes do not feature kicking or punching. The focus is on safe grappling technique that can be done on a daily basis with no more fear of injury than any other contact sport. \r\n\r\nBJJ is most strongly differentiated from other martial arts by its greater emphasis on ground fighting. Commonly, striking-based styles spend almost no time on groundwork. Even other grappling martial arts tend to spend much more time on the standing phase.\r\n\r\nBJJ focus on submissions without the use of strikes while training allows practitioners to practice at full speed and with full power, resembling the effort used in a real competition. Training methods include technique drills in which techniques are practiced against a non-resisting partner; isolation sparring, commonly referred to as positional drilling, where only a certain technique or sets of techniques are used, and full sparring in which each opponent tries to submit their opponent using any legal technique. \r\n\r\n','Brazilian Jiu Jitsu Classes','','publish','closed','closed','','regular-classes','','','2016-08-17 14:07:06','2016-08-17 13:07:06','',0,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?page_id=21',0,'page','',0),(22,1,'2016-02-07 23:50:16','2016-02-07 23:50:16','//TODO','Regular Classes','','inherit','closed','closed','','21-revision-v1','','','2016-02-07 23:50:16','2016-02-07 23:50:16','',21,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/2016/02/07/21-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(23,1,'2016-02-07 23:53:06','2016-02-07 23:53:06','//TODO','Our Students','','publish','closed','closed','','our-students','','','2016-02-07 23:53:06','2016-02-07 23:53:06','',0,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?page_id=23',0,'page','',0),(24,1,'2016-02-07 23:53:06','2016-02-07 23:53:06','//TODO','Our Students','','inherit','closed','closed','','23-revision-v1','','','2016-02-07 23:53:06','2016-02-07 23:53:06','',23,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/2016/02/07/23-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(25,1,'2016-02-07 23:53:48','2016-02-07 23:53:48','','White Belts','','publish','closed','closed','','white-belts','','','2016-02-07 23:53:48','2016-02-07 23:53:48','',0,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?page_id=25',0,'page','',0),(26,1,'2016-02-07 23:53:48','2016-02-07 23:53:48','','White Belts','','inherit','closed','closed','','25-revision-v1','','','2016-02-07 23:53:48','2016-02-07 23:53:48','',25,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/2016/02/07/25-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(27,1,'2016-02-07 23:53:56','2016-02-07 23:53:56','','Blue Belts','','publish','closed','closed','','blue-belts','','','2016-02-07 23:53:56','2016-02-07 23:53:56','',0,'http://localhost/source