PM. Weekend classes are set up for 12PM to 2PM. \r\n\r\nOn <strong>Tuesdays </strong>we train BJJ GI (with the traditional kimono). You are not required to own a kimono to attend to these classes, but we highly recommend that, after some classes, you should acquire one. We have been placing orders to one of the most famous BJJ online store quite frequently in order to help you through the acquisition of your first kimono. \r\n\r\nOn <strong>Thursdays </strong>we train BJJ no GI. (Here is a good link which describes the differences between BJJ GI x BJJ no GI: <a href=\"http://breakingmuscle.com/brazilian-jiu-jitsu/to-gi-or-not-to-gi-differences-between-gi-no-gi-grappling\" target=\"_blank\">To Gi or Not To Gi: Differences Between Gi & No-Gi Grappling</a>)\r\n\r\nOn <strong>Saturdays </strong>we train MMA. (Full-contact combat sport that allows both striking and grappling, both standing and on the ground, using techniques from other combat sports and martial arts)\r\n\r\n<blockquote>Sparring gear is provided at the gym. But you can also bring your own. </blockquote>\r\n\r\n<strong>Payment Options</strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>€35 for 5 classes</li>\r\n	<li>€10 for a single class</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','Classes and Payment Options','','publish','closed','closed','','classes-and-payment-options','','','2016-08-17 14:06:58','2016-08-17 13:06:58','',0,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?page_id=94',0,'page','',0),(95,1,'2016-08-17 14:05:26','2016-08-17 13:05:26','','Classes and Payment Options','','inherit','closed','closed','','94-revision-v1','','','2016-08-17 14:05:26','2016-08-17 13:05:26','',94,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?p=95',0,'revision','',0),(96,1,'2016-08-17 14:06:58','2016-08-17 13:06:58','<strong>Classes</strong>\r\n\r\nClasses at Westside Gym are taught every Tuesday, Thursday and Saturday. \r\nFor weekdays classes are up from 8PM to 9:30PM. Weekend classes are set up for 12PM to 2PM. \r\n\r\nOn <strong>Tuesdays </strong>we train BJJ GI (with the traditional kimono). You are not required to own a kimono to attend to these classes, but we highly recommend that, after some classes, you should acquire one. We have been placing orders to one of the most famous BJJ online store quite frequently in order to help you through the acquisition of your first kimono. \r\n\r\nOn <strong>Thursdays </strong>we train BJJ no GI. (Here is a good link which describes the differences between BJJ GI x BJJ no GI: <a href=\"http://breakingmuscle.com/brazilian-jiu-jitsu/to-gi-or-not-to-gi-differences-between-gi-no-gi-grappling\" target=\"_blank\">To Gi or Not To Gi: Differences Between Gi & No-Gi Grappling</a>)\r\n\r\nOn <strong>Saturdays </strong>we train MMA. (Full-contact combat sport that allows both striking and grappling, both standing and on the ground, using techniques from other combat sports and martial arts)\r\n\r\n<blockquote>Sparring gear is provided at the gym. But you can also bring your own. </blockquote>\r\n\r\n<strong>Payment Options</strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>€35 for 5 classes</li>\r\n	<li>€10 for a single class</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','Classes and Payment Options','','inherit','closed','closed','','94-revision-v1','','','2016-08-17 14:06:58','2016-08-17 13:06:58','',94,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?p=96',0,'revision','',0),(97,1,'2016-08-17 14:07:06','2016-08-17 13:07:06','<strong>Overview</strong>\r\n\r\nBrazilian Jiu Jitsu promotes the concept that a smaller, weaker person can successfully defend against a bigger, stronger assailant by using leverage and proper technique.\r\n\r\nMany students first learn about jiu jitsu through the great popularity of mixed martial arts (MMA) competition, where Brazilian Jiu Jitsu technique is very prominent. Indeed, the beginnings of the contemporary MMA competition were largely tied up with proving the combat-efficiency of Brazilian Jiu Jitsu. \r\n\r\nThe practice of Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu as a sport, however, is strongly separated from MMA. Daily classes do not feature kicking or punching. The focus is on safe grappling technique that can be done on a daily basis with no more fear of injury than any other contact sport. \r\n\r\nBJJ is most strongly differentiated from other martial arts by its greater emphasis on ground fighting. Commonly, striking-based styles spend almost no time on groundwork. Even other grappling martial arts tend to spend much more time on the standing phase.\r\n\r\nBJJ focus on submissions without the use of strikes while training allows practitioners to practice at full speed and with full power, resembling the effort used in a real competition. Training methods include technique drills in which techniques are practiced against a non-resisting partner; isolation sparring, commonly referred to as positional drilling, where only a certain technique or sets of techniques are used, and full sparring in which each opponent tries to submit their opponent using any legal technique. \r\n\r\n','Brazilian Jiu Jitsu Classes','','inherit','closed','closed','','21-revision-v1','','','2016-08-17 14:07:06','2016-08-17 13:07:06','',21,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?p=97',0,'revision','',0),(98,1,'2016-08-17 14:08:05','2016-08-17 13:08:05',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','98','','','2016-08-17 15:49:07','2016-08-17 14:49:07','',0,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?p=98',11,'nav_menu_item','',0),(99,1,'2016-08-17 14:09:47','2016-08-17 13:09:47','','Programs','','publish','closed','closed','','programs','','','2016-08-17 14:09:47','2016-08-17 13:09:47','',0,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?p=99',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(100,1,'2016-08-17 14:11:52','2016-08-17 13:11:52','Mixed martial arts (MMA) is a full-contact combat sport that allows both striking and grappling, both standing and on the ground, using techniques from other combat sports and martial arts. \n\n','Mixed Martial Arts','','inherit','closed','closed','','19-autosave-v1','','','2016-08-17 14:11:52','2016-08-17 13:11:52','',19,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?p=100',0,'revision','',0),(101,1,'2016-08-17 14:12:34','2016-08-17 13:12:34','Mixed martial arts (MMA) is a full-contact combat sport that allows both striking and grappling, both standing and on the ground, using techniques from other combat sports and martial arts. \r\n\r\nOriginally promoted as a competition to find the most effective martial arts for real unarmed combat, competitors from different fighting styles were pitted against one another in contests with relatively few rules. \r\n\r\nLater, individual fighters employed multiple martial arts into their style. MMA promoters were pressured to adopt additional rules to increase competitors\' safety, to comply with sport regulations and to broaden mainstream acceptance of the sport.\r\n\r\nFollowing these changes, the sport has seen increased popularity with a pay-per-view business that rivals boxing and professional wrestling.','Mixed Martial Arts','','inherit','closed','closed','','19-revision-v1','','','2016-08-17 14:12:34','2016-08-17 13:12:34','',19,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?p=101',0,'revision','',0),(102,1,'2016-08-17 15:59:44','2016-08-17 14:59:44','','Jiu Jiteiros','','publish','closed','closed','','jiu-jiteiros','','','2016-08-17 16:36:42','2016-08-17 15:36:42','',0,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?p=102',5,'nav_menu_item','',0),(103,1,'2016-08-17 16:06:56','2016-08-17 15:06:56','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start writing!','Welcome to our','','inherit','closed','closed','','1-revision-v1','','','2016-08-17 16:06:56','2016-08-17 15:06:56','',1,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?p=103',0,'revision','',0),(104,1,'2016-08-17 16:07:34','2016-08-17 15:07:34','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start writing!','Welcome!','','inherit','closed','closed','','1-revision-v1','','','2016-08-17 16:07:34','2016-08-17 15:07:34','',1,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?p=104',0,'revision','',0),(105,1,'2016-08-17 16:08:40','2016-08-17 15:08:40','We have launched our newest website. We hope to keep it up to date as much as possible! \r\nPlease come over for a visit, first training day is free! \r\n\r\nTeam Andre Ramos midwest.','Welcome!','','inherit','closed','closed','','1-revision-v1','','','2016-08-17 16:08:40','2016-08-17 15:08:40','',1,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?p=105',0,'revision','',0),(106,1,'2016-08-17 16:20:48','2016-08-17 15:20:48','','brazil-flag','','inherit','open','closed','','brazil-flag','','','2016-08-17 16:20:48','2016-08-17 15:20:48','',1,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/brazil-flag.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(107,1,'2016-08-17 16:21:07','2016-08-17 15:21:07','<img src=\"http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/brazil-flag-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"brazil-flag\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-106\" />\r\n\r\nWe have launched our newest website. We hope to keep it up to date as much as possible! \r\nPlease come over for a visit, first training day is free! \r\n\r\nTeam Andre Ramos midwest.','Welcome!','','inherit','closed','closed','','1-revision-v1','','','2016-08-17 16:21:07','2016-08-17 15:21:07','',1,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?p=107',0,'revision','',0),(108,1,'2016-08-17 16:35:17','2016-08-17 15:35:17','<ul>\n	<li><a href=\"http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?page_id=25\">White Belts</a></li>\n	<li>Blue Belts</li>\n	<li>Purple Belts</li>\n	<li>Brown Belts</li>\n	<li>Black Belts</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n','Meet the Team','','inherit','closed','closed','','13-autosave-v1','','','2016-08-17 16:35:17','2016-08-17 15:35:17','',13,'http://localhost/source-archive/andreramosbjj/?p=108',0,'revision','',0),(109,1,'2016-08-17 16:36:05','2016-08-17 15:36:05','<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http: